{
  "stem": "2435.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All of the, or many of the friends of my father and mother, who were Jewish and did not get a visa yet to emigrate, kept together very closely.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were able to come yet together, and, of course, they lived under constant fear, just like my parents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were discussing what could one do.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, we were actually very lucky in that way, that my father knew Professor Einstein in Princeton, who had emigrated quite a long time before, in '33, and who had written to the Consulate.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Many of the people did not have that, and were eventually taken to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But due to the fear and constant isolation one lived in Berlin, there was another problem which arised and that was I was very upset about the whole condition there, and became, physically as well as emotionally, ill.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And didn't want to-- I couldn't work any more, I didn't want to eat, I couldn't sleep, and I just wanted to get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the main thing was my condition-- you see, I needed a certificate of good health, which was to accompany the visa, but I couldn't get it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So for a long time, my parents asked some doctors with whom I was in treatment to write out a certificate of good health.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there was a very old, old doctor-- I think he was over 90 years-- whom my father's father knew already.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he wrote out a certificate of good health, which was required for the visa.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My parents finally got their visum in September 1940.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And at that time, my-- but I couldn't get it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But at that time, my brother tried to get out.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
